  "title": "Ship Repair Manager",
  "description": "<p>* Troubleshoot and Formulate repair plan basis the RFQ.</p><p>* Prepare repair estimates, inspection reports, and technical assessments.</p><p>* Supervise hull repairs, steel renewal, and structural fabrication works.</p><p>* Oversee mechanical repairs for engines, pumps, valves, and hydraulic systems.</p><p>* Coordinate daily repair work according to docking schedule and project plan.</p><p>* Liaise with ship owners, superintendents, surveyors, and class societies.</p><p>* Allocate manpower, tools, and materials required for repair operations.</p><p>* Ensure all work complies with marine standards and classification requirements.</p><p>* Enforce workplace safety procedures following shipyard and MOM regulations.</p><p>* Conduct toolbox meetings, risk assessments, and safety briefings.</p><p>* Monitor progress of repair work and provide status updates to stakeholders.</p><p>* Support commissioning and sea trials when required.</p><p>* Prepare daily reports, job completion documentation, and material usage records.</p><p>* Assist in preparing cost summaries, variation orders, and final repair reports.</p>",
